(56, 'contact', 'staff', '11', '4', '<div class=" employeeImgContainer">\r\n		<img class="img-circle center-block" src="/resources/images/dept/marcyK.jpg"/>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=""></div>', '<div class="employeeDescription center-block">\r\n\r\n<h4>Personal Care Administrator </h4>\r\n<h1>Marcy Kerzic</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Marcy has been with Forest City Nursing and Rehab since 2003. She began her career after graduating from the University of Scranton; she later obtained her Masterâ€™s Degree in Healthcare Administration from St. Joseph&#39;s College.  Marcy began her employment in the Activities Department and worked her way up to become the Activities Director.  Marcy has most recently  moved into the Personal Care Administrator role after obtaining her Nursing Home and Personal Care Home Administrator&#39;s licenses.  In her free time, Miss Kerzic enjoys volunteering for various causes both in her own community and others. She has led various fundraising drives for The American Diabetes Association, Cookies for Kids Cancer, Susan G. Komen Breast Cancer Research, The American Heart Association, Griffin Animal Shelter, Shafferâ€™s Homeless Retreat, and Lauraâ€™s Hope Rescue. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(57, 'contact', 'staff', '12', '4', '<div class=" employeeImgContainer">\r\n		<img class="img-circle center-block" src="/resources/images/dept/mattR.jpg"/>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=""></div>', '<div class="employeeDescription center-block">\r\n\r\n<h4>Director of Environmental Services </h4>\r\n<h1>Matthew Rizzo</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Matthew graduated from Seton Catholic High School Pittston, PA. He received an Associates Degree from Luzerne County Community College in Commercial Art with a Specialization in Graphic Design. He also earned a Bachelor of Fine Arts from the University of the Arts, Philadelphia, PA. Matthew has been a team leader with Healthcare Services Group at our facility for two years. Matt greatly enjoys camaraderie with the residents. In his spare time he participates in a dart league, plays recreational softball, and collects and operates RC cars. </p>\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(58, 'services', 'skilledNursing', '1', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4>Short and Long Term</h4>\r\n<h1> Skilled Nursing </h1>\r\n<h4>A person centered approach to wellness</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '<p>For those individuals who require 24-hour medical supervision and can no longer safely remain in their home, we offer professional skilled nursing services. The facility is overseen by multiple practicing physicians and a licensed nursing staff. This team of professionals provides individuals safety and peace of mind that all their medical needs are promptly attended to. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our goal is to bring individuals to their highest level of functioning. Our caring staff and home-like environment provide a warm, compassionate atmosphere for our long-term and short term residents.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(59, 'services', 'skilledNursing', '3', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4>A Multidisciplinary Approach to </h4>\r\n<h1>Dementia Care </h1>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '<p> Maintaining quality of life is the main goal when caring for individuals with dementia. We promote the highest form of well-being by providing a personally tailored plan of care that individually targets the needs of those who suffer from dementia. Take comfort in knowing your loved one will reside in a safe and secure environment under a staff specially trained for dementia care.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Non-Pharmaceutical approaches are first used when addressing the behavioral needs of dementia patients. Through the use of daily sensory based activities we aim to evoke cognitive stimulation. Interventions are person centered and adjusted according to meet the individual&#39;s needs.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(60, 'services', 'rehabilitation', '2', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4>Achieving Independence Requires</h4>\r\n<h1>Dynamic Rehabilitation</h1>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n</div>', '<p>Whether you have just undergone surgery or are recovering from a hospital stay, rehabilitation is paramount to restoring you to your previous state of independence. The therapy department at the Forest City Nursing & Rehab Center provides skillful rehabilitation services that will help you get back to where you want to be. While you focus on healing, we will take care of the small stuff, like laundry, housekeeping, and meal preparations all while providing you around the clock assistance whenever you may need it.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(61, 'services', 'hospice', '1', '1', '<img class="center-block" src="/resources/images/hospice.jpg">\r\n', '\r\n<h1>Hospice Care</h1>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<p> It is not easy to care for a terminally ill loved one. The stresses that are associated with caring for a loved one suffering from terminal illness can be enough to wear at the most steadfast of people. Knowing what to expect and what you can do to increase your loved one&#39;s comfort can help ease concerns. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the Forest City Nursing Center, we understand your concerns and we have devoted two private hospice suites for your dedicated care. With these facilities, you and your loved one are given a comfortable and tranquil space that has round-the-clock care intended to ease the symptoms associated with their illness.</p>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a href="/information/admissions" class="btn btn-maroon">Schedule a Tour Today <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span></a>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(62, 'services', 'rehabilitation', '1', '5', '<div id="carousel-example-generic" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">\r\n								  <!-- Indicators -->\r\n								  <ol class="carousel-indicators">\r\n								    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>\r\n								    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="1"></li>\r\n								    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="2"></li>\r\n								  </ol>\r\n								\r\n								  <!-- Wrapper for slides -->\r\n								  <div class="carousel-inner" role="listbox">\r\n								  	\r\n								  	<div class="item active" id="rehabSlide1">\r\n								      <div class="carousel-caption">\r\n								       <h5></h5>\r\n								       <h2></h2>\r\n								      </div>\r\n								    </div>\r\n								    <div class="item" id="rehabSlide2">\r\n								      <div class="carousel-caption">\r\n								       <h1> </h1>\r\n								      </div>\r\n								    </div>\r\n								    <div class="item" id="rehabSlide3">\r\n								      <div class="carousel-caption">\r\n								        <h1> </h1>\r\n								        <h4></h4>\r\n								      </div>\r\n								    </div>\r\n								    \r\n								  </div>\r\n								\r\n								  <!-- Controls -->\r\n								  <a class="left carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="prev">\r\n								    <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>\r\n								    <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>\r\n								  </a>\r\n								  <a class="right carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">\r\n								    <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></span>\r\n								    <span class="sr-only">Next</span>\r\n								  </a>\r\n								</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(63, 'services', 'rehabilitation', '3', '6', '<div class="col-md-12">\r\n\r\n<h1> Some of the Therapies We offer: </h1>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Physical Therapy </strong> is responsible for the evaluation, treatment, and discharge planning of patients. In physical therapy, the patient will participate in an individualized recovery plan aimed at maximizing patient&#39;s independence and safety during all mobility tasks through patient/caregiver education, gait training, bed mobility, and wound care. We offer services to a variety of patientâ€™s including rehabilitation following a fracture or joint replacement, acute medical conditions, Parkinson&#39;s care, stroke recovery, diabetic rehabilitation, Alzheimer&#39;s/dementia, and general rehabilitation due to weakness or physical decline. We also offer a comprehensive home evaluation assessment with both primary caregivers and the patient to ensure optimal discharge planning.  </p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Occupational Therapy</strong> helps to restore your independence and pre-level of functioning post fall, stroke, or other illness affecting physical activities.  Our Occupational Therapists develop an individual treatment plan to ensure you meet your recovery goals.  Occupational Therapy addresses self care, meal prep, home management, and medication management.  Most importantly however, Occupational Therapy gets you back to your daily routine so you are able to once again engage in activities that have personal meaning and are satisfying to you.  Our Occupational Therapy team is especially exceptional at treating hand and shoulder injuries and has ten years in depth training regarding effective treatment techniques.        </p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row1 -->\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Speech & Language Pathologists </strong> work with individuals who struggle with cognition including memory, attention, and problem solving.  As people age, so do their chances of acquiring a communication or swallowing related disorder. In addition, the chances of an individual in the geriatric population having a stroke, Parkinson&#39;s disease, or developing dementia increase and subsequently so do the chances of acquiring a communication or swallowing disorders related to these diseases. A speech therapist that works with the geriatric population will have the training to detect the difference between disorder and normal aging of the swallowing, voice and cognitive functions.  Speech & Language Pathologists promote a healthy lifestyle and educates consumers on how to prevent stroke and other disorders that may lead to impairment.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<!--<p><strong>Restorative Therapy</strong> services include both physical and occupational therapies where residents are working with licensed therapists in a goal-based program. Many times this program is offered to restore function following a surgery or illness. After completing the program, many residents move into a maintenance program, tailored to their specific needs.</p>-->\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row2 -->\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<!--<p><strong>Restorative Nursing Care</strong> refers to our popular maintenance program, which helps residents maintain as much independence as possible.\r\nWorking with therapy aides on an individualized plan, residents work through strengthening, stretching and mobility exercises in an effort to maintain range of motion, balance and general physical ability.</p>-->\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row3 -->\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'contentTile', NULL),
(64, 'services', 'skilledNursing', '4', '5', '<div class="col-md-12">\r\n\r\n<h1> Some of the Therapies We offer: </h1>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Physical Therapy </strong> is responsible for the evaluation, treatment, and discharge planning of patients. In physical therapy, the patient will participate in an individualized recovery plan aimed at maximizing patient&#39;s independence and safety during all mobility tasks through patient/caregiver education, gait training, bed mobility, and wound care. We offer services to a variety of patientâ€™s including rehabilitation following a fracture or joint replacement, acute medical conditions, Parkinson&#39;s care, stroke recovery, diabetic rehabilitation, Alzheimer&#39;s/dementia, and general rehabilitation due to weakness or physical decline. We also offer a comprehensive home evaluation assessment with both primary caregivers and the patient to ensure optimal discharge planning.  </p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Occupational Therapy</strong> helps to restore your independence and pre-level of functioning post fall, stroke, or other illness affecting physical activities.  Our Occupational Therapists develop an individual treatment plan to ensure you meet your recovery goals.  Occupational Therapy addresses self care, meal prep, home management, and medication management.  Most importantly however, Occupational Therapy gets you back to your daily routine so you are able to once again engage in activities that have personal meaning and are satisfying to you.  Our Occupational Therapy team is especially exceptional at treating hand and shoulder injuries and has ten years in depth training regarding effective treatment techniques.        </p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row1 -->\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<p><strong>Speech & Language Pathologists </strong> work with individuals who struggle with cognition including memory, attention, and problem solving.  As people age, so do their chances of acquiring a communication or swallowing related disorder. In addition, the chances of an individual in the geriatric population having a stroke, Parkinson&#39;s disease, or developing dementia increase and subsequently so do the chances of acquiring a communication or swallowing disorders related to these diseases. A speech therapist that works with the geriatric population will have the training to detect the difference between disorder and normal aging of the swallowing, voice and cognitive functions.  Speech & Language Pathologists promote a healthy lifestyle and educates consumers on how to prevent stroke and other disorders that may lead to impairment.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<!--<p><strong>Restorative Therapy</strong> services include both physical and occupational therapies where residents are working with licensed therapists in a goal-based program. Many times this program is offered to restore function following a surgery or illness. After completing the program, many residents move into a maintenance program, tailored to their specific needs.</p>-->\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row2 -->\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-5">\r\n<!--<p><strong>Restorative Nursing Care</strong> refers to our popular maintenance program, which helps residents maintain as much independence as possible.\r\nWorking with therapy aides on an individualized plan, residents work through strengthening, stretching and mobility exercises in an effort to maintain range of motion, balance and general physical ability.</p>-->\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-1"></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div> <!-- /.row3 -->\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'contentTile', 'contentTile'),
(65, 'index', 'index', '6', '6', '<h2>Hear What Others Are Saying</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class="row testimonials">\r\n<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n  <p>"When it was no longer possible to continue caring for my mom at home, she became a resident at Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center. I immediately felt comfort and peace knowing that her physical and emotional needs were being met by the professional and qualified staff at the facility. Forest City is one of the nicest and cleanest facilities in the area. I would recommend Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center to everyone." </p>\r\n  <footer>Lori Casmer <cite title="Source Title">Browndale, Pa</cite></footer>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n  <p>"My mother ,Yolanda has been a resident at Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center for the past 3 years. My family has been pleased with her care at the facility. If we had any concerns they were handled promptly and to our satisfaction. My mother has been happy with the caring and loving staff and has made many friends. She especially enjoys all of the activities at the center.I would recommend the Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center to anyone who has a need for rehabilition or short or long term care." </p>\r\n  <footer>Joseph Scotchlas<cite title="Source Title"> Simpson, Pa</cite></footer>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="col-sm-4">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n  <p>"I have had trouble walking for quite some time. In early July I fell on my back which left me with internal injuries and intense pain. My granddaughter recommended that I go to Forest City Nursing & Rehab Center for treatment. Having heard that Forest City has one of the best therapy services in the area, I decided to give it a try. My accommodations at Forest City Nursing Center were superb! The nurses, CNAs and other personnel were very caring and saw to my every need. I had extensive Physical Therapy, several times per day and before long I was walking the halls with a walker. The PT Department was well trained and handled my case professionally. If not for the treatment I got at Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center, I would not be walking independently today."</p>\r\n  <footer>Mary M . Podrosky<cite title="Source Title"> Jessup, Pa</cite></footer>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'contentTile testimonials hidden-xs', 'testimonials hidden-xs'),
(67, 'information', 'employment', '4', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4>Meet Activity Aide</h4>\r\n<h1>Cindy Edwards</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>"I&#39;ve worked at Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center since 2009  in the Activity Department. As an activity aide, I assist the Activity Director in enriching the lives of our residents by socializing with the residents. We hold exciting activities daily, including manicures, exercise classes, musical entertainment, picnics, games, religious services, and much more. Our residents have given their best to this country, their families, and their communities and I feel honored to be part of their lives."</p>\r\n\r\n</div>', '<img class="center-block img-circle" src="/resources/images/dept/cindyE.jpg">', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(68, 'contact', 'staff', '13', '4', '<div class=" employeeImgContainer">\r\n		<img class="img-circle center-block" src="/resources/images/dept/brandyS.jpg"/>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=""></div>', '<div class="employeeDescription center-block">\r\n\r\n<h4>Director of Rehabilitation </h4>\r\n<h1>Brandi Schiavone</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Brandi Schiavone DOR, has been our Director of Rehabilitation since 2011. Prior to her management role, she has been a staff occupational therapist here since 2005. She is a graduate of Misericordia with a Master of Science in Occupational Therapy and has spent the past 15 years working in all therapy settings with a true niche for skilled nursing/long term care. While Brandi considers the Forest City Nursing and Rehab Center her home away from home, she enjoys spending time in her actual home at Crystal Lake with her husband John and three children: Darien, Alyvia and Jake. </p>\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(69, 'index', 'index', '4', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4><i>Did You Know...</i></h4>\r\n<h1>You Have The Right to Choose</h1>\r\n<h4>your health care provider </h4>\r\n</div>', '<div class="textBlockContainer">\r\n<p>\r\nWhen you require hospital care and are in need of rehabilitation upon discharge, say <strong><i>YES</i></strong> to Forest City Nursing & Rehab Center. It&#39;s <strong>Your</strong> health and <strong>You</strong> have the final say in choosing where to receive your rehabilitation therapies. We can provide you with high quality of service in the areas of: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p>Speech Therapy</p></li>\r\n<li><p>Occupational Therapy</p></li>\r\n<li><p>Physical Therapy</p></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWe offer pleasant surroundings, professional staff, and a caring atmosphere.\r\n\r\nWith three levels of care all on one campus, Forest City Nursing & Rehab Center is the right choice. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(70, 'personalcare', 'admissions', '2', '1', '<div class="tileHeadingText">\r\n<h4>Helpful Hints:</h4>\r\n<h1>New Admission Checklist</h1>\r\n<h4>Makes Your Transition Effortless</h4>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n</div>', '<p>If you or your loved one are preparing for admission into our Personal Care home, print a copy of this list of items you should bring prior to your admission date.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Admission Checklist</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul style="list-style-type:circle">\r\n<li><p>Copy of Power of Attorney </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Copy of Advanced Directives and/or Living Will </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Insurance Cards </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Medicare Card </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Social Security Card </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Drivers License or Photo ID </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Check including Security Deposit and Prorated First Monthâ€™s Rent </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Medication List (with diagnosis, allergies, immunization history, last progress note) + Medications  </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Desired Personal Clothing (labeled) and Belongings  </p></li>\r\n<li><p>Contact NEP, Located on Main Street in Forest City if You Wish to have a Landline </p></li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
(71, '', '', '4', '5', '<p>We offer continuing care services of Personal Care and Skilled Nursing and Rehab. The Personal Care, a 36 bed facility and the Skilled Nursing and Rehab, a 132 bed facility are available services as your level of care increases. We are able to meet your needs as you age with grace on one campus.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Services Include: </h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><p>Convenient parking</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Daily recreational activities</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Central heating and air conditioning</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Electricity</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Water</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Clothes washer and dryer</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Lawn care</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Snow removal</p></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOur suites are furnished with comfortable beds, chairs, dressers and lamps; however, we invite our clients to bring items that will complement their personal likes and reflect the decor that portrays their individual taste.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOutdoor amenities included beautifully decorated twin porches conveniently accessible from the dining room and community room.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Suites Include:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><p>Carpeted floors</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Private tiled bathrooms</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Wardrobe closet</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Access to cable television</p></li>\r\n	<li><p>Access to telephone</p></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'contentTile'),
